	<!-- Kinetic Monk -->
	<element name="Kinetic Monk" type="Class" source="Kinetic Monk" id="ID_KINETIC_MONK">
		<description>
			<p>The Kinetic Monk is a master of energy in motion, a warrior who channels kinetic force from their own body and the world around them to strike, evade, and control the battlefield.</p>
			<p>Every step, every blow, every motion is a calculated effort to generate potential, store it, and release it with lethal precision.</p>
			<p>These monks do not seek balance through stillness, but through a constant dance of movement and attack. Some train in distant temples where each strike is a meditation on the flow of energy, while others hone their craft atop city rooftops and in crowded streets.</p>
			<h3>CLASS FEATURES</h3>
			<p>As a Kinetic Monk, you gain the following class features.</p>
			<h5>HIT POINTS</h5>
			<p>
				<span class="emphasis">Hit Dice:</span> 1d8 per Kinetic Monk level.<br />
				<span class="emphasis">Hit Points at 1st Level:</span> 8 + your Constitution modifier.<br />
				<span class="emphasis">Hit Points at Higher Levels:</span> 1d8 (or 5) + your Constitution modifier per Kinetic Monk level after 1st.<br />
			</p>
			<h5>PROFICIENCIES</h5>
			<p>
				<span class="emphasis">Armor:</span> None.<br />
				<span class="emphasis">Weapons:</span> Simple weapons, martial weapons<br />
				<span class="emphasis">Tools:</span> Artisan's tools or a musical instrument.
			</p>
			<p>
				<span class="emphasis">Saving Throws:</span>Strength, Dexterity.<br />
				<span class="emphasis">Skills:</span> Choose two from skills Acrobatics, Athletics, History, Insight, Religion and Stealth.
			</p>
			<h5>EQUIPMENT</h5>
			<p>You start with the following equipment, in addition to the equipment granted by your background:</p>
			<ul>
				<li> <i>(a)</i> a martial melee weapon, or <i>(b)</i> any simple weapon. </li>
				<li> <i>(a)</i> a diplomat's pack or <i>(b)</i> an explorer's pack. </li>
			</ul>
